s in the United States, and new organizations for human and civil rights in democratic Argentina. The book concludes with a statistical analysis of the impact of civil society on a set of contemporary democracies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aCivil society. 0aPolitical participation. 4aPolitics -- Comparative and International Politics. 4aSociology -- Social Movements, Civil Society, and Politics. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080476728640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804767286423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804767286/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles